<html>
	<head>
		<title>Metadata</title>
	</head>

<p>These tags are within the head tags in an html document.  Gives the browser or web services information that does not get displayed.</p>

<xmp style="padding:0px;margin:0px;">
	<head>
		<title>While included in the head tag, title isn't meta</title>

		<!-- You can do pretty much anything with this -->
		<meta name="metapage" content="Some description of the page">

		<!-- HTTP headers that are sent to the browser before the content -->
		<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8">

		<!-- The Base tag creates a base URL for resolving relative URLs.
		     This is used so when the page gets visited, all relative links will use that URL as the current page. -->
		<base href="index.html">

		<!-- Links are used to define documents -->
		<link rel="index" href="/var/www/index.html"/>
	</head>
</xmp>

</html>
